 Identify a method to incorporate contexts into the search adapter of Shopping List:

As a Document Engine developer, I want to investigate and identify a viable method for incorporating specialty/condition contexts into the Shopping List search adapter, So that the adapter can scope and filter results based on contextual parameters, ensuring only clinically relevant records are returned for a given shopping list request.

The Shopping List API endpoint will receive structured requests that may include document types, timeframes, and specific clinical concepts tied to a context. The search adapter must be able to consume and act on these contextual parameters when querying for matching OSM records.

Acceptance Criteria


All candidate context parameters are identified and listed (e.g. document type, specialty, condition, timeframe, concept identifiers)

Each parameter is fully specified with name, data type, required vs. optional status, accepted values or format, and a plain-language description
